	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000959_0001"/><!--pb/@n='189-1'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">5<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Feb<hi rend="sup">y</hi> 1857</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Sir William Hooker</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>As I have 
<lb/>at last got hold 
<lb/>of my seeds and 
<lb/>hope to be able to 
<lb/>arrange them in a 
<lb/>day or so. Will 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000959_0002"/><!--pb/@n='189a-2'--> 
<lb/>you kindly drop 
<lb/>me one line to this 
<lb/>address to say by 
<lb/>what conveyance 
<lb/>I can send them<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I have some 
<lb/>fibrous tissue 
<lb/>which I wish 
<lb/>you to examine 
<lb/>also some leaves 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000959_0003"/><!--pb/@n='189a-3'--> 
<lb/>and unripe pods 
<lb/>of a tree which 
<lb/>I suppose to be 
<lb/>a Cinchonaceous one 
<lb/>as it has been 
<lb/>used by the Portuguese 
<lb/>as such in <term type="ailment">fever</term>
<lb/>and by the natives 
<lb/>and myself. I have 
<lb/>some of the bark 
<lb/>of the root <unclear cert="low">iris</unclear><reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_000959_0004"/><!--pb/@n='189-4'-->
<lb/><p>Excuse my troubling 
<lb/>you now. I have 
<lb/>lost so many things 
<lb/>by conveyances 
<lb/>that I like to use 
<lb/>caution<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Believe me &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
			
